tion.";i:4;s:157:"Knee strengthening exercises can be done sitting in a chair by extending your legs one at a time at a slight angle reaching both hands underneath your thigh.";i:5;s:57:"Sit straight in the chair with your legs in front of you.";i:6;s:45:"Now turn to the side and sit facing the left.";i:7;s:118:"Now go through these warrior poses with your arms to the ceiling while on the left then turn and do them to the right.";i:8;s:104:"Keep your right leg to the side of the chair but take your left leg and swing it to the backside of you.";i:9;s:62:"Grab yourself two stable chairs and stand between their backs.";i:10;s:87:"Rest one hand on each back to help you balance then extend one leg out in front of you.";i:11;s:79:"Keeping your weight in the heel of your standing leg slowly lower a few inches.";i:12;s:60:"Raise to standing then repeat for 10 to 15 reps on each leg.";i:13;s:67:"Some researchers say that inflammation plays a role in the process.";i:14;s:75:"1 If you have osteoarthritis its really important to keep moving the knees.";i:15;s:64:"In the video below Ill guide you in an easy chair yoga exercise.";i:16;s:77:"Its designed to reduce the pain and improve joint motion and quality of life.";i:17;s:105:"To help strengthen your knees focus on moves that work your hamstrings quadriceps glutes and hip muscles.";i:18;s:114:"The standing hamstring curls are a great knee exercise and will act to engage your hamstrings and gluteal muscles.";i:19;s:102:"Stand with your knees one or two inches apart and hold on to a stable chair or countertop for balance.";i:20;s:104:"Slowly bend one knee behind your body lifting the heel from the floor while keeping your thighs aligned.";i:21;s:79:"Seated Knee Extension To strengthen your thigh muscles quadriceps The exercise.";i:22;s:20:"Sit on chair or bed.";i:23;s:77:"Straighten knee as far as you can then slowly bend knee as far as it will go.";i:24;s:106:"_____ times each leg Hamstring Stretch To stretch the hamstrings tendons in back of the knee The exercise.";i:25;s:46:"Sit on couch or bed with one leg out straight.";i:26;s:46:"Try these warm-up chair exercises for seniors.";i:27;s:94:"Sit up straight and slowly tilt your head toward your right shoulder until you feel a stretch.";i:28;s:80:"Hold this position while gradually extending your left arm down and to the side.";i:29;s:56:"You should feel a stretch on the left side of your neck.";i:30;s:51:"Clasp your hands and hold them out in front of you.";i:31;s:65:"Bend at the knees pushing out your hands a little as you go down.";i:32;s:52:"Your knees should not bend beyond a 45 degree angle.";i:33;s:93:"Make sure that you push your back outwards as you bend so that you keep your weight balanced.";i:34;s:27:"Do not allow your knees to.";i:35;s:107:"This exercise will not only help strengthen your knees but also make it easier to get in and out of chairs.";i:36;s:37:"For this exercise youll need a chair.";i:37;s:61:"Sit down on the chair and move close to the edge of the seat.";i:38;s:71:"Place both of your feet on the floor keeping them shoulder-width apart.";i:39;s:55:"Keep the knee cap and toes pointing toward the ceiling.";i:40;s:127:"Keeping the knee in contact with the towel straighten the affected leg and SLOWLY lift the heel off the surface over 2 seconds.";i:41;s:91:"Hold the leg as straight as it will go for 5 seconds then SLOWLY lower down over 2 seconds.";i:42;s:50:"Slowly sit up from the chair until fully standing.";i:43;s:91:"Check the knee placement when moving from sitting to standing so they arent bending inward.";i:44;s:70:"Instead they should be projecting outward from the middle of the body.";i:45;s:94:"This exercise requires using the hips not the knees to thrust the body to a standing position.";i:46;s:20:"Benefit of Exercise.";i:47;s:115:"This exercise is beneficial after acute knee surgery by creating a muscle pump to reduce swelling in the lower leg.";i:48;s:51:"Sit in a chair with your back against the backrest.";i:49;s:32:"Maintain a good upright posture.";i:50;s:34:"Place both feet flat on the floor.";i:51;s:87:"Raise both your heels of the floor Your forefoot and toes should still be on the floor.";i:52;s:95:"Sit on the edge of the chair with legs bent at the knees 90 degrees and feet flat on the floor.";i:53;s:58:"Hold the chair or the armrest with your hands for support.";i:54;s:38:"Lean back keeping your spine straight.";i:55;s:72:"Lift both legs up toward your chest keeping your legs bent at the knees.";i:56;s:34:"Then lower your legs to the floor.";i:57;s:29:"Repeat the exercise 30 times.";i:58;s:14:"Stand back up.";i:59;s:19:"You can start slow.";i:60;s:90:"Start with quarter or half squats and build up to full squats as your knees grow stronger.";i:61;s:42:"This exercise is just what it sounds like.";i:62;s:65:"Sit down slowly in a chair then slowly rise to standing position.";i:63;s:33:"Start slowly with a higher chair.";i:64;s:34:"To make it harder use a low chair.";i:65;s:50:"Top 14 Leg Exercises for Seniors with Bad Knees 1.";i:66;s:40:"First on this list is the ankle circles.";i:67;s:55:"Take note that good ankles mean good ankle flexibility.";i:68;s:36:"Knee Extension Seated Leg Extension.";i:69;s:80:"Next on the best leg exercises for seniors with bad knees is the knee extension.";i:70;s:27:"Alternate sides and repeat.";i:71;s:52:"Stand up straight and hold onto the back of a chair.";i:72;s:89:"While bending your right knee lift your right foot as far as you can towards your glutes.";i:73;s:31:"Hold for three to five seconds.";i:74;s:33:"Try doing 10-15 reps twice a day.";i:75;s:41:"Be sure to keep your upper body straight.";i:76;s:70:"Slowly bend your knees and keep your back and pelvis against the wall.";i:77;s:22:"Hold for 5-10 seconds.";i:78;s:21:"Dont bend too deeply.";i:79;s:70:"If you feel pressure or discomfort in your knees change your position.";i:80;s:81:"With all these said the following are 8 exercises for arthritis in knees and hip.";i:81;s:57:"This is one of the good exercises for arthritis in knees.";i:82;s:69:"It is also a great exercise for people who want to build leg muscles.";i:83;s:41:"How to Do Chair Stand for Knee Arthritis.";i:84;s:74:"For these exercises choose a solid stable chair that does not have wheels.";i:85;s:90:"You should be able to sit with your feet flat on the floor and knees bent at right angles.";i:86;s:60:"Avoid chairs with arms as these will restrict your movement.";i:87;s:58:"Wear loose comfortable clothing and keep some water handy.";}}